This paper deals with bias in word embeddings, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and related topics. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to debias word embeddings, which suggests that it could also fit into the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of conceptors, which are a mathematical tool used in control theory, indicating that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CY (Control and Systems Engineering). Finally, the paper evaluates its method using the Word Embedding Association Test (WEAT), which is a common evaluation metric for bias in word embeddings, suggesting that it could also fit into the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
